    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="774"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114 Mail/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-31">August 31,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received August 31—2:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5379. American interests Japan. Department’s 1067 [<hi rend="italic">1967</hi>],
                    August 16.<note n="15" xml:id="d774fn15">Not printed.</note> Swiss
                    representative, Tokyo, informs Legation Japanese Minister Foreign Affairs<note
                        n="16" xml:id="d774fn16">Mamoru Shigemitsu.</note> states he would take
                    necessary measures transmit next exchange vessel correspondence of POW’s,
                    civilian internees as well as 25-word messages from American citizens Far East.
                    Japanese Government expects reciprocal treatment and requests confirmation that
                    American Government will transmit next exchange vessel communications of types
                    mentioned from Japanese in United States.<note n="17" xml:id="d774fn17">In
                        telegram No. 2152, September 2, to the Minister in Switzerland, the
                        Department stated it was “giving correspondence from Japanese in United
                        States reciprocal treatment as requested.”</note>
                </p>
                <p>Gaimusho<note n="18" xml:id="d774fn18">Japanese Foreign Office.</note>
                    communicated identical proposal British Government concerning British subjects
                    Far East.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
